Ask HN: How do I come back after burn-out?
text:
My last job burnt me out so hard that I needed to leave without finding another job.

I've pieced my mind back together in the mean-time (I'm no longer depressed/suicidal), but I still have severe anxiety issues and haven't worked in four years.

The nervousness that results from the anxiety tanks every interview I do, and I never even get to the technical stage (leaving me unable to even display the fact that I do actually know what I'm doing).

I really have no clue how to get back into things.

Ask HN: Can web pages force Casting to other screens?
text: I've had a person report and send me a video that Chrome would begin casting what seemed to be a Instagram web page to a smart tv on the same wi-fi network, while his screen was sitting idle on a Chrome blank page. Unfortunately it was a shared wi-fi and he doesn't know where that TV is. This is inferred from a popup appearing out of the Cast icon(?) next to Chrome's three-dots menu, whose first line is "instagram.com". I've instructed him to disable casting via chrome's flags, and am trying to understand whether private information could have leaked from this and how that happened. My guess for now would be "Web Presentation API" alongside a Instagram page misbehavior, in that case I imagine someone may have seen that web page and that alone, but am unsure as I'm knowledgeable on the Web protocols. Or, in a worse scenario, someone in that wi-fi managed to force this action.
